    <text>
        <body>
      
		<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New York</placeName>&#44; <date>June 15&#44; B 49</date></p>
		<p><hi rend="underline">32 C</hi></p>
		<p><addressee>Mr. Isaac Leeser</addressee>&#44;</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>.</p>
		<p>Dear Sir&#58;</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">I have withdrawn from the fold of Jewish literature in<lb/> your favor and I hope we will remain to be friends or perhaps<lb/> become friends.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">I write to urge you to attach my Hebrew Catalogue to<lb/> your Occident. I would send you by express the necessary copies.<lb/> I furthermore <sic>askyou</sic> to forward me by return mail six of your<lb/> Tefilloth with English translation for German and Polish Jews.<lb/> I have sold five. If you have some in dark maroquin leather or<lb/> more expensive copies send two of <sic>themand</sic> four for &#36;2.50.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">I ask you again to do something&#44; even if it is something<lb/> small for my publishing company and to give me your orders. It<lb/> would be well&#44; if you would do it soon for I may not have on hand<lb/> what you need and may have to send for it. Or it may be necessary to<lb/> have it bound.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">Do you know somebody who wants to sell German type at<lb/> a reasonable price&#63; I need such type right away.</p>
          <p rend="indent(2)">Yours very truly&#44;</p>
          <p rend="indent(3)"><persName role="author">ISIDOR BUSH</persName></p>
		<p>Addressed&#58; <addressee>Revd. Mr. Isaac Leeser</addressee>&#44; Editor of the Occident&#44; etc. etc.<lb/> <placeName>Philadelphia&#44; Pa.</placeName></p>
          
        </body>
